jc - JSON Convert `iftop` command output parser

Usage (cli):

    $ iftop -i <device> -t -B -s1 | jc --iftop

Usage (module):

    import jc
    result = jc.parse('iftop', iftop_command_output)

Schema:

    [
      {
        "device":                   string,
        "ip_address":               string,
        "mac_address":              string,
        "clients": [
          {
            "index":                integer,
            "connections": [
              {
                "host_name":        string,
                "host_port":        string,   # can be service or missing
                "last_2s":          integer,
                "last_10s":         integer,
                "last_40s":         integer,
                "cumulative":       integer,
                "direction":        string
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
        "total_send_rate": {
          "last_2s":                integer,
          "last_10s":               integer,
          "last_40s":               integer
        }
        "total_receive_rate": {
          "last_2s":                integer,
          "last_10s":               integer,
          "last_40s":               integer
        }
        "total_send_and_receive_rate": {
          "last_2s":                integer,
          "last_10s":               integer,
          "last_40s":               integer
        }
        "peak_rate": {
          "last_2s":                integer,
          "last_10s":               integer,
          "last_40s":               integer
        }
        "cumulative_rate": {
          "last_2s":                integer,
          "last_10s":               integer,
          "last_40s":               integer
        }
      }
    ]

